cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.LG

The paper deals with the combination of model checking and automated theorem proving, which are both topics related to logic and formal methods. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also introduces an extended computation tree logic and a proof system, which are related to programming languages and formal methods, making cs.PL (Programming Languages) another likely category. The verification process is completely automatic, which is related to software engineering, making cs.SE (Software Engineering) a possible category. The paper also discusses the design choices that lead to efficiency, which is related to artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible category. Finally, the experimental results are compared to existing state-of-the-art tools, which is related to machine learning and data analysis, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible category as well.
